# Neurex Git Commits and Pull Requests

Operational policy for commits and pull requests in this repository. Format follows [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/). Authoring guide: [git-commit-rules.mdc](git-commit-rules.mdc). Layout: [project-structure.mdc](project-structure.mdc).

```
<type>(<scope>): <description>

[optional body]

[optional footer]
```

Imperative mood, lowercase subject, no trailing period. Prefer ≤ 72 characters in the subject.

---

## Authorization

| Action | Allowed when |
|--------|----------------|
| `git commit` | User **explicitly** requests a commit (or user rules override) |
| `git push` | User **explicitly** requests push — do not offer push proactively |
| `gh pr create` / open PR | User **explicitly** requests a pull request |
| `git commit --amend` | User rules allow (unpushed HEAD, hook fixed files, user said amend) |
| `push --force`, `reset --hard`, etc. | User explicitly requests and understands impact |
| `git config` | Never |

If intent is unclear (“save this”, “finish up”, “ship it”), confirm whether the user wants file changes only, a commit, push, or a PR. Stage only paths for the current task unless the user approves a broader commit.

---

## Commit types

| Type | Use for |
|------|---------|
| `feat` | New component, CLI behavior, token layer, registry item |
| `fix` | Incorrect install, resolver, validation, or runtime behavior |
| `docs` | `docs/`, [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md), package READMEs — no logic change |
| `test` | `packages/*/test/**` |
| `refactor` | Internal restructure, same intended behavior |
| `chore` | Tooling, deps, formatting, repo hygiene |
| `build` | `tsup`, turbo, generated artifact wiring |
| `ci` | CI workflows |
| `perf` | Measurable performance win |
| `style` | Formatting or class order only |

Use `docs` for documentation-only work, not `feat`.

---

## Scopes in this repository

pnpm workspace: `apps/*`, `packages/*` ([pnpm-workspace.yaml](../../pnpm-workspace.yaml)). Pick **one primary scope** per commit from where most lines changed (`git diff --stat`).

| Scope | Paths |
|-------|--------|
| `tokens` | `packages/tokens/` |
| `ui` | `packages/ui/` |
| `registry` | `packages/registry/` (`src/`, `templates/`, `scripts/`) |
| `cli` | `packages/cli/` |
| `playground` | `apps/playground/` |
| `docs` | Multiple files under `docs/` or cross-package documentation |
| `repo` | Root `package.json`, `turbo.json`, `pnpm-workspace.yaml`, workspace scripts |
| `cursor` | `.cursor/rules/**` |
| `agents` | [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md), `.agent/` (gitignored locally) |

Optional nested doc scopes when one doc area dominates: `docs(tokens)`, `docs(cli)`, `docs(registry)`.

**Avoid as scope:** component names (`button`, `dialog`), vague `tests` — use `test(<package>)` instead.

**Multi-package workflow:** prefer separate commits (`feat(ui)` → `feat(registry)` → `feat(tokens)`). After `packages/ui` changes that affect install templates, run `pnpm registry:sync` before or note it in the registry commit body. After token generator changes, note `pnpm --filter @neurex/tokens generate:styles` when registry style outputs depend on it.

---

## Breaking changes

Mark with `!` or `BREAKING CHANGE:` footer when:

- `neurex.config.json` shape or default paths change
- Package `exports` or public entrypoints change
- Token rules become build-failing and invalidate consumer CSS
- Bundled registry item files or `target` paths change

Details: [Conventional Commits — breaking change](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/#commit-message-with-description-and-breaking-change-footer).

---

## Before committing

1. `git status --short` and `git diff` (and `git diff --staged` if needed)
2. `git log -5 --oneline` for message style
3. Exclude unrelated files, `.env`, credentials, accidental `dist/` unless intentional
4. Match scope to [project-structure.mdc](project-structure.mdc) ownership
5. Do not use `git add -A` unless the user wants everything
6. No `--no-verify` unless the user explicitly requests it
7. No interactive git (`-i`)

---

## Commit commands

```bash
git status --short
git diff
git diff --staged
git log -5 --oneline
git add -- <path>
git restore --staged -- <path>
git restore -- <path>
```

Commit (after authorization; HEREDOC on Unix):

```bash
git commit -m "$(cat <<'EOF'
type(scope): short summary

Optional body.

EOF
)"
```

On PowerShell, use a quoted multi-line `-m` or equivalent the shell supports.

