## Pull requests

Use repository templates from [.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE/](../../.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE/). Do not invent a one-off PR body when a template applies.

### Choose a template

| Template | Use when |
|----------|----------|
| [lite.md](../../.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE/lite.md) | Small PRs: docs-only, single-file chores, tiny fixes, low risk |
| [full.md](../../.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE/full.md) | Multi-package work, tokens/registry/cli, UI + template sync, breaking changes, or architectural impact |

When unsure, use `full.md`.

### Base branch

**Default PR target is `dev`, not `main`.**

| Branch | Role |
|--------|------|
| `dev` | Integration branch — open feature/fix PRs here |
| `main` | Production/release — only when the user explicitly requests a PR to `main` |

GitHub's repository default may still be `main`; do not infer the PR base from `gh repo view` or `origin/HEAD` alone. When the user does not specify a base, use `--base dev`.

### Before opening a PR

Run in parallel:

```bash
git status --short
git diff
git log -5 --oneline
git rev-parse --abbrev-ref HEAD
git diff dev...HEAD
```

Confirm the branch is pushed or push only when the user explicitly requests it.

### Fill the template

1. Read the chosen template file from `.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE/`.
2. Replace HTML comments with concrete content from **all commits** on the branch, not only the latest commit.
3. Check Scope and Change Type boxes that match the diff.
4. Complete Package Boundary, Registry/CLI, Token/Styling, and UI safety sections when those areas are touched; mark **Not applicable** otherwise.
5. Record exact verification commands and results in the Verification table.
6. Delete optional sections that do not apply (per template comments).

PR title should summarize the branch intent; it may differ from a single commit subject when the branch contains multiple commits.

### Create the PR

Use `gh` after the user explicitly requests a PR:

```bash
git push -u origin HEAD
gh pr create --base dev --title "short pr title" --body-file .github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE/lite.md
```

For a filled body, write the completed template to a temporary file or pass a HEREDOC/`--body` string — do not open a PR with unfilled `<!-- -->` placeholders or empty required sections.

If a PR was opened against the wrong base, fix with `gh pr edit <number> --base dev` (or `--base main` when explicitly requested).

Return the PR URL when done. Do not push unless the user explicitly requests it.

